=== Crew ===
Regular directorsÂ [[Neil Marshall]], [[Alex Graves]], [[Alik Sakharov]], and [[Michelle MacLaren]]Â are not returning for Season 5. Notably, this is also the first time since Season 2 that no episodes are directed by the executive producers, [[David Benioff]]Â and [[D.B. Weiss]]. MacLaren's departure also makes Season 5 the first since Season 2 with no female director.Â MacLaren is the only female director who ever worked on the TV series, producing two episodes in Season 3 and another two in Season 4.

[[George R.R. Martin]] stated he would not be writing an episode, as he has done in every previous season, because he wants to focus on finishing ''The Winds of Winter'', the sixth novel in the [[A Song of Ice and Fire|book series]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.zap2it.com/videos/game-of-thrones-george-rr-martin-winds-of-winter-jeyne-westerling-prologue-258382]&lt;/ref&gt;Â Meanwhile, [[Dave Hill]], the formerÂ assistant for Benioff and Weiss and the writer of the [[Histories &amp; Lore]] short videos, was brought forward to write an episode after Benioff and Weiss were impressed with his story ideas involving Olly and Ygritte in the fourth season.

